Heart beating steadily, Cody continued forward, placing each foot carefully. The light the room behind was now almost
entirely gone, and Cody's eyes were not adjusting quickly enough to keep up. "Worst thing that could happen is an
ambush," he muttered, then gritted his teeth in self-reproach. "No ambushes, no ambushes. Just a restaurant. And a
kobold. And a couple of jackals. Might have even been mangy dogs." He thought about that a moment. "Very, very mangy
dogs."
